title: Center (group)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //center// of a group $$G$$ is the set
$$
\{\, c \in G : gc = cg \ \forall g \in G \,\},
$$
i.e. the set of elements that commute with all other elements. It, as well as all of its subgroups, are [[normal subgroups|Normal subgroup]] of $$G.$$